    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-08-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-08-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="21"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d21">
                <head>21. Telegram 359 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d21fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, Central Files, 611.95A251/8–355. Confidential; Niact.
                        Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MWP_1">McConaughy</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_FDN_1">Forman</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1955-08-03">August 3, 1955, 7:10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d21-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d21-1"/>
                <p>359. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                <p>Reference your list of 36 American civilian detainees handed to <persName
                        corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName>. We believe as your talks constitute new
                    stage of discussions regarding Americans detained Communist China you should
                    present <persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName> with full list all Americans
                    we believe being prevented from leaving mainland including Mrs. Huizer, two
                    Romanoffs and Mrs. Bradshaw. Bishop James Edward Walsh authorized by his
                    Maryknoll Mission superior here to leave.</p>
                <p>You should transmit to <persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName> these four
                    names to supplement your lists of Americans being detained and add note that
                    superiors of <pb facs="0070" n="23" type="typeset" xml:id="pg_23"/> Bishop Walsh
                    have now authorized him to leave. If you have definite reason for not submitting
                    this supplementary list, inform Department.</p>
                <p>Case of Lai Mee-sen and other Americans of Chinese race under consideration by
                    Department to determine whether your intervention on their behalf at this time
                    might endanger them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
